<p>SCP-001 “When day breaks” is an event of which the foundation always knew about.<br />
The O5 council hid the information in hope to find a way to save humanity without causing panic.<br />
Site-19 gets destroyed in a breach, and is rebuilt bigger and better, now holding some of the most dangerous SCPs (682,106,096,173 as well).<br />
The SCP-001 occurs, humanity is brought to their knees, including the foundation;<br />
Some MTF squads go rogue, others try to relocate themselves to the nearest structure, Alpha-1 keeps doing their job as O5 council protectors.<br />
Most of the survivors in America start living inside the new massive Site-19, but someone finds out that the O5 knew about SCP-001 all along, and a civil war to overthrow the council starts.<br />
Some MTFs, agents, and researchers remain by the council’s side, others join the rebellion, and ultimately win the war.<br />
The O5s are court martial’d and the control of the foundation is given to a new Administrator.<br />
After 5 years SCP-001 ends and humanity starts to rebuild&#8230;and the memory of the foundation in the minds of the survivors slowly dissolves, turning it into the secret organisation they always were.<br />
The GOC took advantage of the thousands of SCP facilities that were abandoned to kill many killable SCPs and to take under custody those that couldn’t.<br />
The Foundation realised the threat and here starts a new war: The secret war.<br />
At the end, the general of the GOC army is assassinated and the Coalition disbands.<br />
After 30 years, in 2023, humanity is back at it’s original numbers, and the foundation keeps on doing their works&#8230;also taking care of the SCPs escaped 30 years prior.<br />
The New administrator dies and a new one is elected by the foundation.</p>
<p>Yeah&#8230;I watch too many movies</p>

