														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2566751">
									

<p>One of my favourite bits of the wiki was in 1425 : &quot;not all omissions leave helpful little notes behind.&quot; Which made me think. What other omissions are hidden?<br />
<a href="/scp-682">SCP-682</a> isn't that special. Sure it's dangerous and all, but it isn't that bad. So why are we working so hard to destroy it? What is so special about 682? Why does the article state, in the first line of the containment procedures, &quot;SCP-682 must be destroyed as soon as possible&quot;? If you want, you can interpret it as 'This was written in older days, when the Foundation was different'. Or maybe, there's something about 682 that isn't written in the article, something that explains why 682 must be destroyed as soon as possible?</p>
<p>&quot;Special Containment Procedures&quot;. I interpret that as saying that these objects, aside from being anomalous, are more or less unique. What with everything in the foundation-verse, you'd think that there would be at least one werewolf or something locked up. But they aren't given Special Containment Procedures, because they can be easily classified, unlike our SCP objects, which are out of the norm even for anomalous objects.</p>

