			<div class="content" id="post-content-2570937">
									

<blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-682">SCP-682</a> isn't that special. Sure it's dangerous and all, but it isn't that bad. So why are we working so hard to destroy it? What is so special about 682? Why does the article state, in the first line of the containment procedures, &quot;SCP-682 must be destroyed as soon as possible&quot;? If you want, you can interpret it as 'This was written in older days, when the Foundation was different'. Or maybe, there's something about 682 that isn't written in the article, something that explains why 682 must be destroyed as soon as possible?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I've headcanon for that, made long ago upon reading how it's hinted that the Foundation found it after it &quot;kill those farmers&quot;.</p>
<p>So it's invincible alien being, drop out of nowhere in some farm.</p>
<p>It is Foundation universe's Kal-El. And the Foundation is fully aware of it.</p>
<p>Now, the Director is bald, isn't he?</p>

